snippet.title: Betty Boop - Betty Boop's Ker-Choo
snippet.description: Tons of animals pile in to see the races. Koko the clown, Bimbo, and Betty Boop are some of the contestants to enter the race. Everyone seems to be smitten with Betty, but will she be strong in the face of adversity?

snippet.title: Superman 09 - Terror on the Midway
snippet.description: Superman attempts to stop the chaos created when several circus animals escape their cages and restraints, including a giant ape.

snippet.title: Popeye The Sailor 004 - I Eats My Spinach
snippet.description: Popeye walks down the street singing his famous song and ignoring the rough life of the city, being the tough sailor that he is. He throws not just a rock, but a boulder at Olive's window. She comes out of the broken window, and they go to the rodeo to see the great Bluto perform.

snippet.title: YoureWatchingToonJet
snippet.description: ToonJet TV spot

snippet.title: A Christmas Tree
snippet.description: A Russian cartoon. A little boy prepares his Christmas tree as he thinks about his father working in Antarctica where there are no Christmas trees. He wishes he could take his father one, when he tries to catch a taxi to the south pole. Santa Claus lands his sparkling sleigh-like vessel, called the Star Shooter, beside the car and agrees to let the child take it to Antarctica.

snippet.title: Futura High Command - The Firebomb
snippet.description: Colonel Bleep unveils his new invention, the Futurion Robots. They are designed to help run the space station and to function as mechanics. The villain Dr. Destructo watches from afar and vows to blow up the oil wells that keep the robots going.

snippet.title: 3 Stooges - 014 - A Bull for Andamo
snippet.description: The Stooge-Coach Movers are moving a load of bull in the back of their moving van. They zoom past the Mexican border, when they soon discover that the bull is gone out of the back! It is up to the Three Stooges to get him back!

snippet.title: Superman 04 - The Bulleteers
snippet.description: Trivia: In Superman: Doomsday, the restored bullet car appears as one of Superman's trophies in his Fortress of Solitude.

snippet.title: Mel-O-Toons - Hansel and Gretel
snippet.description: Hansel and Gretel decide to go out into the forest to pick strawberries, dropping breadcrumbs as they go so they won't lose their way. But, soon they meet a gold-haired man calling himself the sandman, and strange things begin to happen.

snippet.title: Daffy Duck - A Coy Decoy
snippet.description: Daffy Duck is fooled by a sexy decoy made by the wolf to lure him into a trap.

snippet.title: Merrie Melodies - Fresh Hare
snippet.description: In the Canadian North Woods Bugs is wanted dead or alive and Mountie Elmer is out to bring him in.

snippet.title: Popeye - I'm in the Army Now
snippet.description: Olive tells the boys she loves a man in a uniform, so they try to sign up at the recruiting station, but they can only take one. There follows a duel of clips from previous shorts as they attempt to prove who is the winner.

snippet.title: Clutch Cargo - 008 The Arctic Bird Giant
snippet.description: Clutch and the gang are traveling through the snow, when they see an avalanche begin to come crashing down. Clutch speculates that it may have been caused by someone on purpose. They meet up with Captain Lowtide and board his ship, where they learn his cargo has begun to be stolen by the bird giant.

snippet.title: Felix - Two-Lip Time
snippet.description: Felix chases a mouse onto a ship, gets seasick, and eventually finds himself in Holland. He flirts with a local Dutch girl and angers a local man who hits him in the head with a wooden shoe. He makes a deal with another man for a dish of milk in exchange for watering the man's plants, but Felix accidentally puts gin into the watering can and gets the plants drunk.

snippet.title: Superman 01 - The Mad Scientist
snippet.description: An inventor has built powerful giant robots that can fly like planes and open banks like cans. Of course, Lois Lane gets into trouble with a robot; can Superman rescue her from the inventor's hideout?

snippet.title: ComiColor - Humpty Dumpty
snippet.description: Humpty Dumpty fights the dastardly Bad Egg for Easter Egg's affections. Humpty's mom tells him to stop sitting on high things as he almost cracks his shell just like his dad did. Easter Egg comes along and they go singing. The Bad Egg comes along and Easter Egg turns out to be a pretty good fighter.

snippet.title: Bugs Bunny - Falling Hare
snippet.description: Bugs encounters wartime sabotage and takes to the air to do battle. Bugs Bunny reads in the newspaper that gremlins are sabotaging the war. He laughs, but he soon finds out that the gremlins are real. Bugs runs into his first nemesis to give him a run for his money.

snippet.title: Three Stooges - 015 - The Tree Nuts
snippet.description: The Three Stooges are rangers searching for a lumber thief. It turns out the thief is an unlikely suspect.

snippet.title: Popeye The Sailor 006 - Wild Elephinks (Cartoon)
snippet.description: Popeye sails on the sea with Olive Oyl on a raft. They end up on a deserted island, and meet up with many fierce animals, including lions, gorillas, and elephants. Popeye bonks an elephant in the trunk before it could carry him away, but a gorilla makes off with Olive. Popeye has to chase it down before it does Olive any harm.

snippet.title: Mel-O-Toons - The Magic Clock
snippet.description: In the city of Glickenglocken, an elaborate clock announces each hour with a fanfare and an angel's song. But, the king of the nearby city of Dumberg was not happy with Glickenglocken's prosperity. He aimed to put a stop to their glorious song...

snippet.title: Popeye   Popeye For President
snippet.description: Popeye and Bluto are running for president; it's election day, the vote is tied, and Olive is the only remaining voter. But she won't vote until her chores are done, so Popeye and Bluto compete to cut her wood, plow her fields, and store her hay. And then it's just an old-fashioned fight.

snippet.title: Oswald   Bright Lights
snippet.description: The Shimmy Queen dances at the Vodvil club. Oswald tries to be a big rabbit by getting by the door man, but that doesn't work out so well for him.

snippet.title: Dick Tracy 03 - Jewel Fool
snippet.description: Dick Tracy calls Joe Jitsu to advise him Flattop has stolen a valuable piece of jewelry, a tiara worn by the duchess of Spiffingham. He was last seen at Madame Tussaud's Wax Museum in London, so Joe travels immediately to the wax museum, where he poses as a wax figure to track down Flattop.

snippet.title: Betty Boop - The Impractical Joker
snippet.description: Betty Boop's baking is interrupted by obnoxious practical joking friend Irving. Can Grampy out-joke the joker?

snippet.title: Silly Symphonies - The Night Before Christmas
snippet.description: Eight children sleep snugly in their beds as Santa lands on the roof and sneaks in through the chimney, but not before the flames bite at his backside. He unloads his sack, which contains toy that help decorate the Christmas tree.

snippet.title: Mel O Toons - Little Hawk
snippet.description: Mel-O-Toons version of the story of Little Hawk

snippet.title: Superman Ep. 6 - Volcano
snippet.description: Superman's adventures in saving a small island community from a volcanic eruption.

snippet.title: Mighty Mouse - Wolf! Wolf!
snippet.description: Wolves want to eat a lamb and Mighty Mouse shows up to save the day.

snippet.title: Dick Tracy - 05 - The Oyster Caper
snippet.description: Dick Tracy calls Joe Juitsu to report oyster thieves. He investigates and finds Pruneface has a hand in the caper.

snippet.title: Silly Symphonies - El Terrible Toreador
snippet.description: Somewhere in Mexico, a gentleman of high standing tries to eat his food at a restaurant. A waitress brings him a drink, as he flirts with her. She dances for him and he gives her a coin. He begins making advances on her, and another gentleman comes along, seeing her in distress. He stops the man's advances, and as it turns out, the girl's hero is the Terrible Toreador.

snippet.title: Superman 03 - Billion Dollar Limited
snippet.description: An enormous gold shipment en route to the mint is hijacked by well armed robbers, and Lois Lane is trapped in the runaway locomotive. This looks like a job for Superman...

snippet.title: Willie Whopper - The Air Race
snippet.description: Willie Whopper and his friends are playing when they see a poster for an upcoming air race. He tells his friends of the time when he supposedly raced in one himself.

snippet.title: Betty Boop - Red Hot Mamma
snippet.description: It is cold and snowy outside Betty Boop's house. It is so cold that she has to light a fire and sleep in front of it. She tosses and turns for some time, until she wakes up and finds a gateway to a particular hot place under the earth.

snippet.title: Popeye   Private Eye Popeye
snippet.description: Private Eye Popeye gets a call from Olive Oyl to guard a precious gem. But no sooner does he get the gem than the butler takes it (and Olive). The rest of the cartoon is spent chasing the crook to Paris, the Swiss Alps, and North Africa; Popeye always gets there first, but fails to make the arrest until he lucks into some spinach, of course.

snippet.title: Felix - April Maze
snippet.description: Felix and the kittens' picnics keep getting interrupted by unnatural forces.

snippet.title: Screen Song - The Ski's the Limit
snippet.description: In Switzerland, towns are prosperous in part because of their skiing industries, as well as others such as cheese-making (swiss cheese made by shooting it full of holes with a machine gun), lace-making (where moths eat holes in the cloth) among others. The cartoon ends with the song, "I Miss my Swiss, My Swiss Miss Misses Me."

snippet.title: The Daffy Duckaroo
snippet.description: Daffy Duck rides his donkey across the desert singing a cowboy song, but when he gets seduced by a beautiful indian maiden, he gets sucked into a tale of intrigue.

snippet.title: Felix - Bold King Cole
snippet.description: Felix the Cat is perched in a tree playing his guitar and serenading himself and a canary with a little ditty called "Nature and Me." It is a beautiful day in cartoon-land but Mother Nature, perhaps not a music lover, whips up a lightning-laden thunderstorm and Felix is soon seeking shelter. He finds it at the castle of King Cole, a boastful, fabricating blow-hard. The King's ancestors, tired of hearing the braggart, come out of their pictures as ghostly specters and take the King to the dungeon and pump the gassy hot-air out of him.

snippet.title: Superman 04 - The Arctic Giant
snippet.description: In the Siberian mountains, a Tyrannosaurus Rex is discovered in pristine condition. Scientists bring it back to the United States to thaw it out, reanimating the creature and releasing havoc on the city of Metropolis.

snippet.title: Futura High Command - Col. Bleep's Arrival on Earth
snippet.description: Dr. Destructo had been captured, serving time in a special jail cell. Col. Bleep is on a mission to investigate disturbances on Earth.

snippet.title: Felix - Neptune Nonsense
snippet.description: Felix is feeding his various pets: a bird, two dogs, and a goldfish. But Annabelle the goldfish is unhappy; she's lonely. Felix sets out to catch her a friend. The fish drag him underwater. After a bit of searching, he finds a goldfish, but the fish cries for help, and Felix finds himself on trial before King Neptune. He's accused of wanting to eat the fish, but after he explains himself, Neptune gives him a fish from the fish orphanage, and everyone lives happily.

snippet.title: Popeye - Out to Punch
snippet.description: Popeye's training for his boxing match with Bluto by jumping rope with a massive chain. Bluto, who's lazy about everything except sabotage, decides he needs to stop Popeye. He fills Popeye's heavy bag with iron junk, but Popeye punches it over the fence onto Bluto. Next, he pulls on the springs attached to the wall with a motorcycle, but Popeye pulls so hard he throws Bluto and the cycle through the building and into arnwell. Popeye is walking -- or actually, prancing -- behind Olive on the way to the match, so Bluto tries a bit more sabotage: first an oil slick, which slows Popeye down briefly, then some quick-dry cement in a puddle. This gives Popeye cement overshoes, and when he gets to the arena, he's exhausted. Olive stands him up, but Bluto treats him like a punching bag. He's got Popeye on the floor (under the ring), so Olive finally breaks out the spinach. Popeye knocks Bluto through the roof, right into the hospital. The photographers ask for a picture, and Popeye's biceps form the words "THE END."

snippet.title: Popeye - I Don't Scare
snippet.description: Popeye has beaten Bluto to a date with Olive. Seeing that Olive is superstitious, Bluto changes the date to Friday the 13th, and proceeds to rig various proofs that bad things will happen if she goes out.

snippet.title: Felix Revolts
snippet.description: After enduring various indignities by the human population in town, including getting beaten up by the fish market owner and forced to eat hot mustard by a customer in a restaurant, Felix finally breaks when he hears the mayor give a speech vowing to drive all cats out of town. Felix gathers his feline friends and stages a revolution to restore cats to their rightful place in society.

snippet.title: Hoppity Hooper - 002 - Ring A Ding Spring
snippet.description: Hoppitty travels along with prof. Waldo Wigglesworth and Filmore the Bear, who were trying to sell their Indian Elixer. Hoppitty realizes they were filling the bottles with water from Ring-A-Ding spring, which causes a rock to grow a handlebar moustache, a beard, and hair!

snippet.title: Popeye The Sailor - Sock A Bye, Baby
snippet.description: Popeye pushes a baby down the sidewalk through town, and after being woke up, Popeye gives him a guitar. The baby gets ahold of his pipe as Popeye sings, and eventually falls asleep. Popeye has to find inventive ways to keep the baby from waking up.

snippet.title: Superman 02 - The Mechanical Monsters
snippet.description: A mad scientist unleashes robots to rob banks and loot museums. Superman saves the day. Animation by Steve Muffati and George Germanetti.
